beer.beer_description:
A craft beer for the non-craft beer drinker!

The newest addition to the Loophole Brewing core range is a hybrid between an Australian Draught/Dry and a Golden Ale.

We mashed at a low temperature, like a lager, so it has a dry, crisp finish. No dry-hop, just a little (and by this we mean teeny tiny amount) Galaxy hot-side. Malt: Pale, Munich and Carapils.

It’s a pretty basic, easy drinking beer – just yellow, wet goodness to keep everyone (else) happy.

items.checkin_comment: It is spelt Draught. Not quite as malty as your typical Aussie draught but in a good way, more like home baked bread rather than a soggy multigrain sandwich *cough* red tins *cough*. Its beer that just tastes like real beer, but no rocket science here.
